- 'packet_count' is the total number of packets processed;
- 'mean_latency' is the mean latency calculated;
- 'error_count' is the total number of errors encountered;
- 'node_name' is the name of the network node.

- "average latency" refers to the mean latency calculated for each network node;
- "total packets processed" is the count of performance metric entries for each node;
- "total alerts" is the count of alerts generated for each node.

